---
description: Inspect and operate the full DeployBot delivery pipeline
alwaysApply: false
---

Read `.mergequeue.toml` and use the `deploybot` MCP tools. For full status call
`pipeline_status`; for queue-only status call `queue_plan`; for one pull request
call `inspect_pull_request`. Status requests stay read-only: never freeze a
queue merely to inspect it.

Report metadata-only active threads, deploy intent, PR stages, queue order,
exact heads, blockers, overlap, CI, and deployment. Only the user's exact
`deploy` instruction authorizes `request_deployment` for that thread. Publish
the stable Cursor thread ID, never prompts or transcripts. Refresh intent only
after replacement-head review. Only the coordinator may react, integrate,
drain, follow, pause, or resume repaired work.
